President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster in the State of Hawaii due to severe storms, flooding, and landslides that occurred from December 5 to December 10, 2021. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Benigno Bern Ruiz has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.